commit.message:
Fix #26 - Broken builds for Mageia Linux

Mageia Linux uses wxWidgets 3.2.1 in backwards-compatibility mode
with version 2.8, which then adds an unfortunate (and deprecated
wxToolBarBase::AddTool() overload). Switching from
wxArtProvider::GetBitmap() to wxArtProvider::GetBitmapBundle()
gets around the issue.
